Enabling PV_HDFStore output¶

To enable this output dataformat, call the method self.StorageOptions.ConfigurePandasHDFStore(True) in the Initialization method of a PyVerify test.

Per default, the test will create a HDFStore_data.h5 and HDFStore_wf.h5 file inside the tests result directory.

Converting existing results to PV_HDFStore¶

In [6]:
from pverify import convert_to_pandas_hdfstore
convert_to_pandas_hdfstore(
    source=r"C:\temp\PyVerify\results\Dummies\Avenue_DummyTest\results.hdf5",
    dst_data=r"C:\temp\PyVerify\results\Dummies\Avenue_DummyTest\converted_data.h5",
    dst_wf=r"C:\temp\PyVerify\results\Dummies\Avenue_DummyTest\converted_wf.h5",
    complevel=9,
    complib="blosc"
)

Open/Close a PyVerify HDFStore¶

In [2]:
from pverify import PV_HDFStore, Waveform
In [3]:
DATA_FILE = "HDFStore_data.h5"
WF_FILE = "HDFStore_wf.h5"
In [4]:
h = PV_HDFStore(DATA_FILE, mode="r")
# h.Close()

type name unit dtype description
0 parameter Amplitude A number Base amplitude of oscillation
1 parameter DUT string The device under test (lab) or schematic (sim)...
2 parameter Damping number Damping constant
3 parameter Dummy number Dummy parameter for abort
4 parameter Firmware string Dummy firmware file
5 parameter Frequency Hz number -
6 parameter Offset A number DC current offset
7 parameter Temp deg number The environment temperature used for the test.
8 output dampedOsc A(s) waveform damped oscillating current
9 output energyAvg A number average energy
10 output firmwareCheck number Firmware availability check
11 output loadCurve V(s) waveform load and unload of output voltage
12 output maxLoad V number maximum load voltage

                                   where="Frequency == 8. and Offset == 0.105",
